cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PF 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of throughput fluctuation in CSMA wireless networks. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves the study of communication protocols and their impact on quality of service. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves the development of analytical tools for network design. The paper may also be relevant to the cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) sub-category as it deals with the behavior of multiple agents (links) in a network. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.PF (Performance) as it involves the analysis of network performance in terms of throughput and starvation.
